NUMBER 1045
NAME Foyer
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
REGION 11
*DESCRIPTION_START
Sticky tendrils of dust and sticky webs brush your cheek, draped from the large
wooden ceiling beams. Clouds of dust burst forth from the faded rug with
each step, choking the room with a gray fog. Dull brass wall sconces are
dribbled with wax, the candles they once held now only short blackened wicks.
An oval mirror hangs beside a wooden stairway leading up into darkness.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1046
EXIT W 1047
EXIT E 1063
ITEM 0 943 VAL2=2579 OPEN
ITEM 1 81
ITEM 2 1311 ADJ1=103
ITEM 3 360 ADJ1=105
ITEM 4 362 ADJ1=95
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Badly tarnished, the ornate sconces are now discolored. They hang at odd
angles on the wall, jarred once again as the house shifts.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
Dull red eyes, their color muted by the heavy layer of dust on the mirror,
glint evilly as you gaze into the mirror. A few strips of bloody skin cling
to the bleached bone face staring back at you, its mouth frozen in a cruel
grin.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO 1
  CLEARVERB
   ECHO ALL A ghostly shape appears in the middle of the stairway and pushes %N back to the bottom of the stairs while intoning, "Nay, it is not yet time." The apparition then slowly fades away, but not before casting a sad glance over you.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLIMB 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You can't climb the stairs.
ENDIF
IFVERB SNIFF -1
  ECHO PLAYER A few strands of cobwebs are sucked up into your nostrils as you inhale, causing you to sneeze violently.
  ECHO OTHERS %N sneezes!
ENDIF
  IFVERB LISTEN -1
    ECHO PLAYER You hear the house creaking all around you and faint moans somewhere nearby.
    ECHO OTHERS %N looks worried as %s pauses a moment.
  ENDIF
    IFPREVERB TOUCH 3
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER As you try to wipe some of the dust off the mirror you feel as sharp pain in your hand, as if something had bitten you!
      ECHO OTHERS As %N tries to wipe some of the dust off the mirror %h jumps and yelps in pain.
      DAMAGEPLR SLASH 10 %N is slashed by the mirror!
    ENDIF
      IFPREVERB TOUCH 4
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER As you lift the corner of the rug a cloud of dust billows up, covering you with grime.
        ECHO OTHERS When %N lifts up the rug a cloud of dust billow up, covering %i with grime.
        APPEAR %S is covered with dust and dirt.
      ENDIF
;
NUMBER 1063
NAME Library
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
INDOOR_FLOOR
REGION 11
*DESCRIPTION_START
The old wooden bookcases lined up against the walls shudder and threaten to
dump their contents onto the floor as you enter. Every inch of wallspace has
been used to display the hundreds of volumes covering almost every subject. An
old leather chair rests in the center of the room on a large circular rug, its
covering split and the stuffing spewn on the floor. An old faded painting
leans precariously outwards from the western wall, cobwebs and dust covering
its once bright colors.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 1045
ITEM 0 1028 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=355
ITEM 1 345
MONSTER_GROUP 108
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The books are rotting, and you realize that the slightest touch would make
them crumble into nothing but dust. The wood of the bookcases has been
warped and twisted by the passage of time.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Only faint colors remain of the painting, yet you can vaguely distinguish
two older men standing behind two seated children. One of the men wears
impressively colored robes, while the other wears an impressive set of
polished plate mail. The two children, one male and one female, have faded
to near nothingness, though you can easily make out the jet black color of
their eyes...
*DESCRIPTION_END
VARIABLE jasso
IFENTRY
 IFVAR jasso => 1
   ECHO PLAYER You notice that two books have slid apart on the bookcase, forming a small niche between them.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB2 PUT 0
  CLEARVERB
    IFVAR ARCHNUM = 288
      IFVAR ITEMADJ1 = 95
        REMOVEITEM -1
        ECHO PLAYER You slide the dirty skull into the bookcase, and are quite surprised to find yourself being sucked through the bookcase along with the skull!
        ECHO OTHERS %N slides the dirty skull into the bookcase...and is unable to let go of the skull! %N's body is slowly pulled into the bookcase, disappearing finally with a horrible sucking sound!
        DISBAND
        MOVE 1064
        AFFECT 1064
        ECHO OTHERS %N is pulled into the room.
        AFFECT 1063
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
     IFVAR ARCHNUM ! 288
         ECHO PLAYER %A doesn't seem to fit properly into the bookcase.
         ECHO OTHERS %N frantically tries to stuff %a into the bookcase, but to no avail.
     ENDIF
ENDIF
