NUMBER 1065
NAME Mountain Top
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
REGION 11
CHANNEl 135
*DESCRIPTION_START
You find yourself atop a mountain, on its very peak. The wind blows with
a ferocious savagery, bringing with it swirling flakes of snow that softly
cover the small flat area you find yourself on. Through the drifting snow
you can make out broken tiles upon the flat area, the patterns they once
held long faded so as to make any detail undiscernible.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
  SETEVENT 45 3 ALWAYS
  CONTEVENT 45
  ECHO PLAYER Three figures suddenly fade into view, a tall warrior, a small boy and a small girl. Fear is etched across all of their faces, though the warrior is attempting to soothe the children.\
The little boy looks up at the warrior and says, "Cheydalin, why didn't Cristalos come?", the warrior replies, "Arlan, he had to stay at the house..there was just no other way, now come...We go to Igaronath.". The small\
group then disappears as they seem to pass right through the mountain wall behind them.
  EQUAL INTNUM45 3
  ECHO PLAYER As the figures fade, you also feel yourself being pulled back..
  MOVE 1064
  AFFECT 1064
  ECHO OTHERS %N appears, looking a bit stunned.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2579
NAME Haven, mansion door
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
*DESCRIPTION_START
Brooding malovelence and sickness emanate from the dark house before you.
Its oppressive silence and darkness hanging before you with crushing weight.
A single, stout oaken door guards the mysteries contained within the house.
Behind you the sickly, yellow grass of the front lawn brings the stench of
death and decay to your nostrils...
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 80 ADJ1=294 VAL2=2578
ITEM 1 943 ADJ1=997 ADJ2=447 VAL2=1045 OPEN
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Taking a closer look at the door you notice several faint scratch marks set
into the door, as if someone, or something, had attempted entry. Dried blood
is also present in the marks, and in many spots, the broken fingernails of
those who attempted entry.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB KNOCK 1
  ECHO ALL The door glows brightly, illuminating all in a brilliant white light. When the light fades you see the flickering image of a man's head floating in the center of the door. Ancient and powerful eyes gaze at you before speaking, "Begone you
  echo all plague-ridden scum! None may enter my dwelling!" After this speech the head flickers and fades.
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
  ECHO PLAYER As you look about the area you get the faint impression that you are being watched, yet when you look closer you don't see any signs of anyone.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3959
NAME Sea Cave, water
UNDERSEA
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
The bottom of the lake is surrounded by the same synthetic rock formations
found above, though they are a bit craggier down here. Again there is a
marked lack of the usual flora and fauna found in most fresh-water lakes.
A large opening, leading out to the central cavern chamber, is to the east.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT U 3958
ITEM 0 72 VAL2=3961
VARIABLE vatten
VARIABLE upna
IFVERB SEARCH -1
  RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
  ADD DUMMY1 PER
   IFVAR DUMMY1 => 135
     ADD vatten 1
    IFVAR vatten = 1
      ECHO PLAYER Hidden amongst some craggy outcroppings you spot a large metal wheel!
      ECHO OTHERS %N points excitedly to spot between some craggy outcroppings!
      NEWITEM 1 1024 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=192
    ENDIF
      IFVAR vatten > 1
        ECHO PLAYER The wheel has already been found.
        ECHO OTHERS %N makes a fruitless search for the already found wheel.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
    IFVAR dummy1 < 135
       ECHO PLAYER The weirdly twisting shadows, combined with the water, makes it hard for you to spot anything.
    ENDIF
ENDIF
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The wheel is in remarkably good working condition for having been submerged
so long. It is virtually rust free, and seems as if it would move without
any large effort on your part.
*DESCRIPTION_END
VARIABLE torka
IFPREVERB TURN 1
  ADD torka 1
    IFVAR torka = 1
      ECHO PLAYER The wheel begins to descend a bit into the floor of the cavern...
     ECHO OTHERS %N starts turning the wheel, it begins to descend into the cavern floor a bit....
    ENDIF
    IFVAR torka = 2
      ECHO PLAYER The wheel is almost all the way to the cavern floor now...
      ECHO OTHERS %N's efforts have moved the wheel until it's almost touching the bottom...
    ENDIF
    IFVAR torka = 3
      ECHO PLAYER With a final turn the wheel locks into place and disappears into the cavern floor!
      ECHO OTHERS %N gives the wheel a final twist and it clicks into place and descends into the cavern floor!
      ADD upna 4
      REMOVEITEM 1
      EQUAL torka 0
    ENDIF
ENDIF
MONSTER_GROUP 37
