NUMBER 3963
NAME Sea Cave, water
UNDERSEA
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
This seems to be the deepest reach of the lake. The light from above is
blocked by the large piers and the water has taken on a midnight black
color. It is also a bit colder in this spot than in other sections of the
lake. Numerous pieces of the synthetic like rock lie strewn about the floor
scraped off the walls by something very large rubbing against them.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT U 3962
EXIT W 3961
ITEM 0 1024
IFVERB SEARCH -1
  ECHO PLAYER Hidden inside a small crevice you notice a small wheel affixed to the wall!
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TURN 0
  ECHO PLAYER With some effort you manage to wriggle your hand inside the crevice and turn the small wheel. You spin it once around and then feel\
it lock into place and slide into the wall.
  ECHO OTHERS %N wriggles %h into the crevice and turns a small wheel. After one revolution the wheel locks into place and disappears into the wall.
  ADD upna 3
  REMOVEITEM 0
ENDIF
