NUMBER 3964
NAME Sea Cave, tunnel
UNDERSEA
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
This murky and cold underwater tunnel ends to the north at a gigantic set
of metal doors. The doors take up the whole tunnel wall and have no
discernible means of opening them. The other walls are coated with the same
synthetic rock material found elsewhere in the sea caves. There seems to be
some painting covering the face of the doors.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 3961
ITEM 0 944 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=97 VAL1=2000 VAL2=3965 CLOSED LOCKED
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The painting is of a large, blue globe surrounded by a ring of silver stars.
The ring of stars is set at an 45 degree angle around the globe, and above
the globe is a black silhouette of what looks like a cigar with some
protrusion in the middle.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
 IFITEM 0 OPEN
   ECHO PLAYER The large doors are open.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
